 <text id="F0936T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>H. C. Fortescue, W. H. Etter, and J. A. S. Cromer ask Cameron for a donation.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>
  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Simon Cameron</name>
    </head>
    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1861-01-25"><abbr expan="January">Jann</abbr> 25<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1861</date>
      <name type="place">Chambersburg</name>
     </dateline>
     <salute>To the Hon. Simon Cameron<lb/> Dear Sir--</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>We the undersigned Citizens of Chambersburg desirous of obtaining some <orig reg="useful"
      >usefull</orig> information <orig reg="relative">relitive</orig> to our Country and knowing
     the <unclear>numerous</unclear> quantity of "<hi rend="underline">Book</hi>", You have in your
      <orig reg="possession">posision</orig>, would be exceeding <orig reg="thankful"
     >thankfull</orig> to you for a small donation, <orig reg="such">shuch</orig> as you think best
     suited to our minds. And we will ever pray for your future success, in all your undertakings,
     and for the satisfactory adjustment of our Nation affairs. And,</p>

    <closer>
     <salute>We Remain Your<lb/> Respectfully</salute>
     <signed>H. C. Fortescue<lb/> W. H. Etter<lb/> J. A. S. Cromer</signed>
     <seg type="postscript">Chambersburg Franklin Co <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">P<hi rend="super"
       >a</hi></abbr>
     </seg>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
